      Configuration Routing Rules Redirect Rule Property

variables.description: Name of the host where requests are redirected.
variables.name: HostName

variables.description: The HTTP redirect code to use on the response.
variables.name: HttpRedirectCode

variables.description: The protocol to use in the redirect request.

variables.description: The object key prefix to use in the redirect request. For example, to redirect                   requests for all pages with the prefix docs/ (objects in the                      docs/ folder) to the documents/ prefix, you can set                   the KeyPrefixEquals property in routing condition property to                      docs/, and set the ReplaceKeyPrefixWith property to documents/.
